                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is the very common 'post patch/nerf paranoia' .. it happens everytime there is a significant patch or nerf, and is nearly always proven to be a bad run of the RNG taken out of context.
<br />

<br />
I seriously doubt that any mobs outside of OoW have had new damage tables applied to them (yet, and hopefully never will). So far HoH and Tactics have both had people cry wolf, only to proven wrong.  Any 'feelings' of increased resists etc. in old content are just that 'feelings', and if you put them to the test you'll find nothing has changed.
<br />

<br />
I agree that the current changes to charm are very much a nerf, and with out some kind of change the RvR of charm has been thrown seriously out of balance, however I would like to see us try and keep the complaints based on what was 'actually' broken.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
