This is the whole point of my post, the new charm tables are already being applied to mobs in non-oow zones, in this case, velious.  I believe these mobs are recent additions, but they are nonetheless in dragon necropolis.
<br />

<br />
The mobs are called "A mercenary excavator" and there are 3 nearby as soon as you zone in.  I will gladly post my logs if you'd really like to see them hit for 215 while charmed, and 471 while not, but logs can easily be falsified, take a trip to DN, charm one and see for yourself.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">It aint scalable, most likely its just set manually per mob's level. Say 61-64 will always hit for 245, and 65-67 for 260.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
